sub_dices.name: Which DIY Project will you try?

options.name: Furniture Renewal: Renewing worn-out furniture by painting, polishing or reupholstering.
Handmade Jewellery: Making handmade bracelets, necklaces or earrings using beads, stones, wire or other materials.
DIY Decoration: Making wall hangings, paintings or decorative objects using various materials for home decoration.
Handmade Cards: Making handmade cards to be used on special occasions or events.
Knitting and Sewing Projects: Making a handmade blanket, pillowcase, shawl or dress by knitting or sewing.
Creative Recycling Projects: Making decorative or functional objects using recyclable materials, such as candle holders from old jars.
Stationery and Notebook Making: Making handmade notebooks or diaries, making personalized notebook covers.
Gardening and Plant Care: Growing plants in your own garden or in pots, creating flower arrangements or garden decoration.
Handmade Soap and Cosmetic Products: Making handmade soap, body lotion or lip balm using natural ingredients.
Homemade Food and Beverages: Food and beverage production, such as making homemade bread, jam, pickles, yoghurt or beverages.
Woodworking: Projects using wood materials, such as making furniture, carving, painting wood, or building playsets.
Macrame and Weaving: Making wall hangings, plant hangers or bracelets with macrame technique;
Metal Work: Work using metal materials, such as jewellery making, metalworking art, or welding projects.
Ceramics and Pottery: Making ceramic objects, pottery or sculptures using clay, painting or glazing ceramics.
Photography and Scrapbooking: Making photo albums, decorating scrapbooks, scrapbooking projects or making photo frames.
Nature and Outdoor Activities: Handmade stone painting, sand art or works of art made with natural materials during nature walks.
Electronics and Robotics Projects: Projects related to electronic circuits, robot construction or coding projects.
Glass Works: Glass art projects such as glass mosaic making, glass painting or glass fusion projects.
Accessory and Fashion Design: Making handmade bags, hats or clothes with fabric and materials, accessory design or fabric painting.
Origami and Paper Art: Paper folding projects with origami techniques, paper cutting and gluing art, paper toy or cardboard model making.

Being strong means staying strong even in difficult times and difficult situations.
Love is only as much as you can give.
Failure is an opportunity for a new try.

I don't know something, but I know the way to know it.

Great difficulties enable great souls to grow.
To measure a person's character, give him power.
The amount of money in a person's wallet determines the size of his ideas, not him.
Value knowledge, because knowledge will set you free.
If you can change a person's thoughts, you can change his actions.
Great tasks are tasks that great people can do.
Life is not about how long it is, but how it is lived.

A small step can be the beginning of a big journey.
You don't have to remember everything to understand everything.
True love is not something that makes us weak and powerless, but rather something that makes us strong and courageous.
Life is a constant struggle and this struggle is the sum of the victories won.
Failure just shows that you need to be more careful.
A man's character lies in his self-consciousness.
It is important not to live forever, but to live a life with meaning.
Our difficulties are the teachers that life gives us.
The greatest victory is to triumph over oneself.
To know a person, you have to walk a mile with him.
When you feel defeated, learn to try just one more time.
Success is not falling, but rising again.
Man's character is in his own consciousness.
Everyone has at least one story.
